{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BQjHTvaud19GtiJZqBMpnc","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\n### **index.ts** (Full file)\nKey patterns:\n- **Framework**: Hono (lightweight HTTP server)\n- **CORS**: Unrestricted origin (safe because auth is bearer-token only, not cookies)\n- **Middleware stack** applied via `app.use()`:\n  - Request logging (timing, method, path) with DEBUG level\n  - CORS on all routes\n  - JWT auth on authenticated paths (e.g., `/profile/*`, `/referral/*`, `/coinflip/*`, `/lord/*`, `/challenges/*`, `/points/*`, `/crates/*`)\n  - Rate limiting per-wallet + global on game endpoints\n- **Route registration** via `app.route()`:\n  - Auth (login, challenge-response)\n  - Game endpoints (coinflip, lord, closecall)\n  - Profile & referral (authenticated)\n  - Price, leaderboard, dogpile (public)\n  - Admin routes (only if `ADMIN_TOKEN` set)\n- **Workers started before routes**:\n  - Settlement worker (polling, 1s interval)\n  - PDA watcher (WebSocket instant detection)\n  - Close Call clock worker (minute-boundary oracle settling)\n  - Event queue worker (async side-effects)\n- **Event handlers registered** before worker starts: REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED, GAME_SETTLED, REWARD_POOL_FUND, POINTS_GRANT, CRATE_DROP\n- **Dependencies injected**: `db`, `sql`, `connection`, `serverKeypair`, `config`, workers\n\n---\n\n### **challenges.ts** (lines 1-50)\nFactory pattern: `createChallengeRoutes({ db })` returns a Hono router. Imports `readRewardConfig` from reward-pool-fund handler. Types defined: `ChallengeRow` (id, campaign_id, title, reward_type, reward_amount, etc.), `AssignmentRow` (challenge_id, period_key, status, progress, target, expires_at, completed_at).\n\n---\n\n### **price.ts** (lines 1-30)\nSimple public route. Fetches SOL/USD from Pyth Hermes client. 60s cache with TTL check. Exports `fetchSolPrice()` function used by other handlers (e.g., points grant). No factory pattern; direct module export.\n\n---\n\n### **reward-pool-fund.ts** (Full file)\n**Factory pattern**: `createRewardPoolFundHandler(deps: { db })` returns async handler for REWARD_POOL_FUND events.\n\n**Key function**: `readRewardConfig(db, key)` — queries `reward_config` table by key, returns string value or null. Used at lines 86 and 23 to read \"reward_pool_fee_share\".\n\n**Handler logic**:\n1. Extract `roundId` and `feeLamports` from payload\n2. Read `reward_pool_fee_share` config (float between 0–1)\n3. Calculate funded amount: `floor(feeLamports * share)`\n4. Insert funding record (with ON CONFLICT idempotency guard)\n5. Atomically increment `reward_pool.balance_lamports` and `lifetime_funded`\n6. All within a transaction for atomicity"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"854178fe-49ab-42ba-ac58-41bc6d7d756e","uuid":"271cf987-5283-4aca-a47e-9750c58474f1","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:15:25.340Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read these files and report their contents concisely (key patterns, imports, route registration, middleware usage):\n\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` — full file, focus on how routes are registered and middleware applied\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/challenges.ts` — just the first 50 lines to see the factory pattern\n3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/price.ts` — first 30 lines for route pattern\n4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/reward-pool-fund.ts` — full file, need to see readRewardConfig\n\nReport the full content of index.ts since I need to see all route registrations. For others, summarize the patterns.","agentId":"a6abb579cfd26c3cb","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\n### **index.ts** (Full file)\nKey patterns:\n- **Framework**: Hono (lightweight HTTP server)\n- **CORS**: Unrestricted origin (safe because auth is bearer-token only, not cookies)\n- *