{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gj5iM3voZR8DZFb6zcBaEh","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the complete report.\n\n## Integration Test Structure Report\n\n### 1. **Test Structure (describe, beforeEach, afterAll)**\n\nTests use **Vitest** with the following hierarchy:\n\n```typescript\ndescribe(\"Integration: create → join → settle lifecycle\", () => {\n  let db: Db;\n  let rawSql: ReturnType<typeof postgres>;\n  let mockConn: MockConnection;\n  let app: Hono;\n\n  beforeAll(async () => {\n    // Setup: create db connection, build db instance\n    rawSql = makeSql();\n    db = createDb(DATABASE_URL, rawSql);\n  });\n\n  afterAll(async () => {\n    // Cleanup: close connections\n    await db.close();\n    await rawSql.end();\n  });\n\n  beforeEach(async () => {\n    // Reset state before each test\n    await rawSql`TRUNCATE ...`;\n    // Setup fresh app and mock connection\n    mockConn = new MockConnection();\n    app = new Hono();\n  });\n\n  it(\"test name\", async () => {\n    // Test implementation\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### 2. **HTTP Request Pattern (app.request with JWT)**\n\nAll HTTP requests use the Hono `app.request()` pattern:\n\n```typescript\nconst createRes = await app.request(\"/coinflip/create\", {\n  method: \"POST\",\n  headers: {\n    \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n    \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${token}`,\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify(body),\n});\n\nconst response = await app.request(\"/rounds/{pda}\", {\n  method: \"GET\",\n  headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },\n});\n```\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- `app.request(path, { method, headers, body })`\n- Headers object uses both quoted and unquoted forms (both work)\n- POST requests: include `\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"` header\n- GET requests: only need auth header\n- JWT in every authenticated endpoint\n\n### 3. **TRUNCATE List in beforeEach**\n\n```typescript\nawait rawSql`TRUNCATE rounds, closecall_rounds, closecall_candles, operator_events, event_queue, game_entries, transactions, player_profiles, referral_codes, referral_links, referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates, reward_pool_fundings, point_grants, player_points, dogpile_events, crate_drops, progress_events, challenge_assignments, bonus_completions RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE`;\n```\n\n**Also resets reward pool:**\n```typescript\nawait rawSql`UPDATE reward_pool SET balance_lamports = 0, lifetime_funded = 0, lifetime_paid = 0, updated_at = now() WHERE id = 1`;\n```\n\n### 4. **Latest Test Patterns (Last 2-3 Test Blocks)**\n\nFrom the dogpile and challenges routes (lines 2887-2933):\n\n```typescript\nit(\"GET /dogpile/current returns active event over scheduled\", async () => {\n  // Insert test data\n  await rawSql`\n    INSERT INTO dogpile_events (starts_at, ends_at, multiplier, status)\n    VALUES (now() - interval '1 hour', now() + interval '1 hour', 2.5, 'active')\n  `;\n\n  const res = await dogpileApp.request(\"/dogpile/current\", { method: \"GET\" });\n  expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n  const body = (await res.json()) as Record<string, any>;\n  expect(body.status).toBe(\"active\");\n  expect(body.multiplier).toBe(2.5);\n  expect(body).toHaveProperty(\"id\");\n});\n\nit(\"GET /dogpile/current returns null when no events\", async () => {\n  const res = await dogpileApp.request(\"/dogpile/current\", { method: \"GET\" });\n  expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n  const body = await res.json();\n  expect(body).toBeNull();\n});\n```\n\n**Challenge app tests with pagination:**\n```typescript\nconst res1 = await challengeApp.request(\"/challenges/mine/history?limit=2\", {\n  method: \"GET\",\n  headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },\n});\nconst body1 = (await res1.json()) as Record<string, any>;\nexpect(body1.items).toHaveLength(2);\nexpect(body1.nextCursor).not.toBeNull();\n\nconst res2 = await challengeApp.request(`/challenges/mine/history?limit=2&cursor=${body1.nextCursor}`, {\n  method: \"GET\",\n  headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },\n});\n```\n\n### 5. **JWT Token / Auth Headers (EXACT VERBATIM PATTERN)**\n\n**JWT Generation:**\n```typescript\nasync function makeJwt(wallet: string, userId = userIdFromWallet(wallet)) {\n  const now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);\n  return new SignJWT({ wallet })\n    .setProtectedHeader({ alg: \"HS256\" })\n    .setSubject(userId)\n    .setIssuedAt(now)\n    .setExpirationTime(now + 3600)\n    .sign(JWT_SECRET);\n}\n\nfunction userIdFromWallet(wallet: string) {\n  return `usr_${wallet.slice(0, 8).toLowerCase()}`;\n}\n```\n\n**JWT Secret:**\n```typescript\nconst JWT_SECRET = new TextEncoder().encode(\"test-secret-for-integration-tests\");\n```\n\n**Auth Header in Requests (EXACT PATTERNS):**\n```typescript\n// Pattern 1: Quoted key\nheaders: {\n  \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${token}`,\n}\n\n// Pattern 2: Unquoted key (also used)\nheaders: { \n  Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` \n}\n```\n\n**App Middleware Setup:**\n```typescript\napp.use(\n  \"/coinflip/*\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: JWT_SECRET }),\n);\n\n// Or for routes that require auth on all methods:\nchallengeApp.use(\n  \"/challenges/*\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: JWT_SECRET, requireAllMethods: true }),\n);\n```\n\n**Usage in tests:**\n```typescript\nconst wallet = creatorKeypair.publicKey.toBase58();\nconst token = await makeJwt(wallet);\nconst token = await makeJwt(testWallet, testUserId);  // Custom userId\n\nconst res = await app.request(\"/coinflip/create\", {\n  method: \"POST\",\n  headers: {\n    \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n    \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${token}`,\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify(body),\n});\n```\n\nAll test files use these exact patterns consistently across 2974 lines of integration tests."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"854178fe-49ab-42ba-ac58-41bc6d7d756e","uuid":"1fdd3b82-c4b9-4c30-b825-04431f8b859c","timestamp":"2026-0